🧠 C. News Distribution — Proper Notes
💡 Core Intuition (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 This problem is exactly connected components again

Think:
Users = nodes
If two users are in the same group → they are connected

So:

🔥 Each group forms connections → builds a graph

🧠 Key Observation

If user x starts the news:

It spreads to all users in the same connected component
Because:
friend → friend → friend chain

👉 So answer for user x = size of its connected component

🎯 Final Reduction

Problem becomes:
👉 “Find connected components and print their sizes for each node”

⚡ Approach (DSU)
Step 1: Initialize DSU for n users
Step 2: Process each group

For a group:

k: u1 u2 u3 u4

👉 Connect like:

unite(u1, u2)
unite(u1, u3)
unite(u1, u4)
Step 3: After all unions

Each user belongs to some component

Step 4: For each user

👉 Print:

size of component = size[find(i)]
🔥 Mental Model
Groups → edges → graph → components → sizes
🚀 Code (Clean + Optimal)
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class DSU {
public:
    vector<int> parent, size;

    DSU(int n) {
        parent.resize(n + 1);
        size.resize(n + 1, 1);
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            parent[i] = i;
        }
    }

    int find(int x) {
        if (parent[x] == x) return x;
        return parent[x] = find(parent[x]);
    }

    void unite(int a, int b) {
        a = find(a);
        b = find(b);

        if (a == b) return;

        if (size[a] < size[b]) swap(a, b);

        parent[b] = a;
        size[a] += size[b];
    }
};

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(NULL);

    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;

    DSU dsu(n);

    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int k;
        cin >> k;

        if (k == 0) continue;

        int first;
        cin >> first;

        for (int j = 1; j < k; j++) {
            int x;
            cin >> x;
            dsu.unite(first, x);
        }
    }

    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        cout << dsu.size[dsu.find(i)] << " ";
    }

    cout << "\n";
}
⚠️ Common Mistakes (VERY IMPORTANT)
❌ 1. Forgetting find() while printing
dsu.size[i] ❌

✅ Correct:

dsu.size[dsu.find(i)]
❌ 2. Not handling k = 0

👉 That user stays alone → size = 1

❌ 3. Unioning all pairs (O(n²))
// WRONG
for all pairs in group

✅ Use first element trick → O(n)

📊 Complexity
Total unions ≤ 5e5
DSU → almost O(n)

